Key Match Events: Zach LaVine stole the show for Chicago, dropping 35 points while grabbing 10 rebounds and dishing out eight assists.
Nikola Vučević backed him up with 24 points and 11 rebounds.
Coby White added 23 points and kept the Spurs’ defense on its heels.
Victor Wembanyama finished with 23 points, 14 rebounds, and eight blocks.
Chris Paul scored 18 points and handed out nine assists.
Julian Champagnie drained four three-pointers for 12 points off the bench.
Stephon Castle chipped in 10 points and six assists off the bench.
Post-Match Reflections: Acting head coach Mitch Johnson said after the game, 'You have to impose your will on the game as an individual and as a team. And that's how teams close wins out in this league.'
